article.headline: Holy Cross 42, Northeastern 21
article.story: BROOKLINE, Mass. -- Dominic Randolph threw five touchdown passes to lead Holy Cross to a 42-21 win over Northeastern on Saturday. Randolph was 16-for-24 with 305 yards and an interception for the Crusaders (4-0), throwing touchdown passes to five different receivers. He also rushed for 29 yards on six carries. Holy Cross jumped out to a 21-0 lead after Randolph threw a touchdown pass of 12 yards to Freddie Santana, a 49-yarder to Rob Koster and Matt Bellomo added a 5-yard touchdown run. Randolph's 28-yard passing score to Luke Chmielinski and 13-yard connection to Nick Cole helped Holy Cross claim a 35-7 halftime lead. Randolph's final 17-yard passing score to Alex Schneider put Holy Cross ahead 42-7. Matt Carroll threw a pair of TDs to Jordan Batts in the fourth for the Huskies (0-5). Carroll finished 32-for-44 with 248 yards and three touchdowns.
